    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8bd1de8e_c4fc011a",
        "filename": "vl-android.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 3145,
      "author": {
        "id": 1087048
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-14T16:43:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The other patch calls android_dns_get_servers which in turn gets the system DNS server, doesn\u0027t that mean that we potentially try to get DNS system servers twice if there are no system servers?\n\nI\u0027m probably responsible for some of this but it seems like the DNS responsibilities are a little spread out.",
      "parentUuid": "8b547ee5_d0531ce7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 3143,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 3145,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "f82e37d46f109080786838ca9684bcd796279208",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "eb1b3a59_a353ba10",
        "filename": "vl-android.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 3145,
      "author": {
        "id": 1000411
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-14T16:46:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The other patch rewrites the -dns-server option to resolved IPs, so the second pass will not try to get the system servers, it will just use the ones from the rewrite (be they system servers or actually come from the command-line).\n\nYes, I understand this is a little confusing. I will probably add some comments to the other patch to explain what\u0027s going on.",
      "parentUuid": "8bd1de8e_c4fc011a",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 3143,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 3145,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "f82e37d46f109080786838ca9684bcd796279208",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "8bd1de8e_170ac979",
        "filename": "vl-android.c",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 3145,
      "author": {
        "id": 1087048
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-04-14T17:00:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "But it will only add the option if it actually finds any DNS servers as I understand it. If there are no system DNS servers the scan will be performed twice since dns_addr_count will be zero when the slirp initialization happens.\n\nI don\u0027t really think that\u0027s really problem in terms of performance or anything, it just seems to indicate that the responsibilities are well separated. Since this is QEMU code I don\u0027t feel like that is as important as if it was our own code though.",
      "parentUuid": "eb1b3a59_a353ba10",
